============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Euler's Identity
Branch:       Complex Analysis
Formula:      e^(iπ) + 1 = 0
Applications: Signal processing, quantum mechanics
Discoverer:   Leonhard Euler (1748)

Theorem/Law:  Prime Number Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      π(n) ~ n/ln(n)
Applications: Cryptography, algorithm analysis
Discoverer:   Hadamard/de la VP (1896)

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is machine learning?
A1: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

Q2: What is the Big Bang?
A2: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

Q3: What is inflation?
A3: Inflation is the general rise in price levels over
     time, reducing purchasing power. Caused by excess money
     supply, high demand, or supply shocks. Measured by the
     Consumer Price Index.

Q4: What is the internet?
A4: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q5: What is the periodic table?
A5: The periodic table organizes 118 elements by atomic
     number. Elements in the same column share chemical
     properties. Rows are periods; columns are groups.

